你是说我们得从那爬上去吗  
You mean to tell me that's all we gotta climb?

1264
02:07:07,540 --> 02:07:09,770
还没有训练爬的那么高
They're not as high as the practice ones.

1265
02:07:10,040 --> 02:07:11,770
训练时可没有炮火
They wasn't shooting at us then.

1266
02:07:13,420 --> 02:07:15,800
为什么不让空军或是海军来干  
Why can't the Air Force or Navy do this job?

1267
02:07:16,050 --> 02:07:19,820
从空中看不到悬崖后面掩体内的大炮
The big guns in bunkers behind the cliff can't be seen from the air.

1268
02:07:20,060 --> 02:07:23,290
不干掉它  它就会干掉我们海滩上的弟兄
We knock them out or they'll murder our guys on the beach.

1269
02:07:23,500 --> 02:07:25,260
是啊  要我说的话  
Yeah, well, if you ask me...

1270
02:07:25,470 --> 02:07:28,420
三个老太婆用扫帚就能把我们一扫光
...three grandmothers with brooms could sweep us off there...

1271
02:07:28,630 --> 02:07:30,590
就象从甜饼上轰走苍蝇一样
...like flies off of a sugar cake.

1272
02:14:06,080 --> 02:14:07,950
就是它  我们要找的目标
That's it, the one we're after.

1273
02:15:04,990 --> 02:15:06,290
是空的
It's empty.

1274
02:15:06,760 --> 02:15:10,180
空军和海军确实给了他们好看
The Air Force and Navy really plastered this baby.

1275
02:15:10,500 --> 02:15:11,790
可我没明白
But I don't get- -

1276
02:15:12,730 --> 02:15:14,100
这些炮
The guns.

1277
02:15:14,800 --> 02:15:16,390
都没有架好
There ain't no mounts.

1278
02:15:17,240 --> 02:15:19,400
根本就还没有安装过
They've never even been installed.

1279
02:15:20,740 --> 02:15:21,940
你是说
You mean...

1280
02:15:22,850 --> 02:15:25,770
我们费了这么大的劲  
...we come up all this way...

1281
02:15:26,020 --> 02:15:27,570
却只是一场徒劳  
...for nothing?

1282
02:15:32,690 --> 02:15:34,780
别担心  你不会有事
Don't worry, sarge, you'll be all right.

1283
02:15:35,060 --> 02:15:37,330
医生  医生
Medic! Medic!

1284
02:15:38,810 --> 02:15:40,430
"请别"  "请别"
"Bitte!","Bitte!"

1285
02:15:46,310 --> 02:15:48,730
他叽哩咕噜的在说什么  
I wonder what"Bitte, Bitte" means.

1286
02:15:59,190 --> 02:16:02,920
你穿着救生衣搞什么鬼  
What the hell are you wearing a life preserver for?

1287
02:16:03,560 --> 02:16:05,290
我不会游泳
I can't swim.

1288
02:16:13,440 --> 02:16:17,970
诺曼底  真的是诺曼底
Normandy. It really is Normandy.

1289
02:16:18,780 --> 02:16:22,740
真是疯狂  疯狂  纯粹是疯狂
This is madness, madness, sheer madness!

1290
02:16:24,260 --> 02:16:25,990
什么事  
What is it?

1291
02:16:26,260 --> 02:16:30,490
我刚和约德尔将军通过话  元首已经醒了
I just talked to General Jodl, the Fuhrer is awake.

1292
02:16:30,730 --> 02:16:36,300
我才不在乎他醒没醒  装甲预备队的事怎么样  
I don't care if he's awake or not! What about the reserve panzers?

1293
02:16:37,180 --> 02:16:41,640
元首在大发雷霆  
The Fuhrer went into one of his tantrums...

1294
02:16:42,280 --> 02:16:45,050
所以没人敢提任何事
...and no one dared bring up the subject.

1295
02:16:45,620 --> 02:16:47,780
那就是还处于预备状态
They're still held in reserve!

1296
02:16:48,390 --> 02:16:50,520
是的  元帅
Yes, field marshal.

1297
02:16:53,130 --> 02:16:56,520
长官  如果你亲自打给元首  
Sir, if you would call the Fuhrer yourself...

1298
02:16:56,930 --> 02:17:00,290
我相信他会尊重你的看法
...I am convinced he would respect your views.

1299
02:17:00,640 --> 02:17:02,070
打给他  
Call him?

1300
02:17:02,310 --> 02:17:05,160
打给那个波希米亚下士  
Call that Bohemian corporal?!

1301
02:17:06,150 --> 02:17:09,480
要我向他奴颜卑膝  
Crawl on my knees to him?!

1302
02:17:10,150 --> 02:17:12,780
不  连想都不要想
No! It is out of the question!

1303
02:17:16,330 --> 02:17:21,920
"用单调的忧郁刺伤我的心"
"Wounds my heart with a monotonous languor."

1304
02:17:22,370 --> 02:17:23,420
什么意思  
What's that?

1305
02:17:23,700 --> 02:17:26,970
没什么  已经没有意义了
Nothing, nothing of importance.

1306
02:17:28,880 --> 02:17:30,570
来  我来帮你
Here, let me help you.

1307
02:17:31,750 --> 02:17:34,910
你还好吧  汤姆  快  他们在上边
You all right, Tom? Come on, they're up there.

1308
02:17:39,220 --> 02:17:41,110
-头  -怎么
- Sir. - Well?

1309
02:17:41,420 --> 02:17:44,760
史密斯要我转告你  他的人已准备好
Mr. Smith says to tell you he's stood his men too.

1310
02:17:45,000 --> 02:17:49,350
德军带着机枪和迫击炮推进到了树林里
The Jerries are moving up into the woods... ...with machine guns and mortars.

1311
02:17:50,240 --> 02:17:53,260
-要弟兄们做好准备  -告诉弟兄们　　
- Tell the men to stand firm! - Tell the chaps- -

1312
02:17:53,470 --> 02:17:56,570
准备应付敌人下一轮猛烈反攻
Tell them to expect another counterattack, a heavy one.

1313
02:18:00,980 --> 02:18:03,010
-拿着伙计  -谢谢
- Here you are, mate. - Ta.

1314
02:18:06,990 --> 02:18:08,720
-什么事  -听　　　
- What's the matter? - Listen.

1315
02:18:08,890 --> 02:18:10,780
我听到了风笛声
I thought I heard bagpipes.

1316
02:18:11,000 --> 02:18:12,860
别傻了
Don't be daft!

1317
02:18:21,740 --> 02:18:24,730
我告诉你听到了风笛声  是援兵
I told you I heard bagpipes! It's the reinforcements.

1318
02:18:38,900 --> 02:18:39,960
是拉瓦特
It's Lovat!

1319
02:18:47,940 --> 02:18:49,270
快
Come on!

1320
02:18:49,850 --> 02:18:51,300
快
Come on!

1321
02:19:18,320 --> 02:19:20,440
-抱歉来晚了  -比不来要好
- Sorry I'm late. - Better than never, sir.

1322
02:19:20,650 --> 02:19:22,050
真高兴见到你  希米
Glad to see you, Shimmy.

1323
02:19:26,830 --> 02:19:29,990
你们正好被当成了靶子  情况如何  
You boys are right on target. What's the situation?

1324
02:19:30,200 --> 02:19:33,120
德军在一英里外的树林中重新部署
Jerry's regrouping in the woods, about a mile.

1325
02:19:33,500 --> 02:19:35,270
有迫击炮和重机枪
With mortars and heavy machine guns.

1326
02:19:35,500 --> 02:19:36,560
有多少  
Numbers?

1327
02:19:36,840 --> 02:19:40,500
不知道  希米  但似乎正在集结更多兵力
No idea, Shimmy, but they seem to be moving forward in force.

1328
02:19:42,380 --> 02:19:44,010
那样的话  我们就更不能等了
In that case, we won't wait.

1329
02:19:44,850 --> 02:19:46,210
最好还是行动
We'd better get moving.

1330
02:19:46,850 --> 02:19:48,740
好了  我们要穿过去
All right, we're going across.

1331
02:19:48,990 --> 02:19:50,180
-米林  -是
- Millin! - Sir?

1332
02:19:51,020 --> 02:19:52,620
吹"黑熊"
"Black Bear," sir.

1333
02:19:53,090 --> 02:19:55,360
好了  来吧
All right, come on.

1334
02:19:55,560 --> 02:19:57,020
都起来
Everybody up!

1335
02:19:57,570 --> 02:19:59,020
出发
On your feet!

1336
02:20:05,410 --> 02:20:08,540
是他  他又在吹了
There he goes. He's at it again.

1337
02:20:08,910 --> 02:20:11,640
你这辈子听过这么难听的声音吗  
Ever hear such a bleeding racket in all your life?

1338
02:20:11,880 --> 02:20:14,610
没错  爱尔兰人吹风笛就是这样
Yeah, it takes an Irishman to play the pipes.

1339
02:20:30,210 --> 02:20:32,340
坚守至援兵到来
Hold until relieved.

1340
02:20:32,610 --> 02:20:34,310
坚守至援兵到来
Hold until relieved.

1341
